{"TopicId":119951,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.5] Cormorant Aeronology - Mk3 Space Shuttle","CreatedByName":"Pak","CreatedById":141068,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-09-02T05:40:31Z","PageNum":80,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-07T14:31:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541547133\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sslaptnhablhat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, sslaptnhablhat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side-note, what mod is that Canadarm1 from? Also, how ya getting on with TNiC?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8930183000\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/118906-11x-canadarm-v171-5-june-2016/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Eaten by Black Hole","CreatedById":192333,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T09:24:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223482554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541547133\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sslaptnhablhat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/7/2018 at 2:32 AM, sslaptnhablhat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side-note, what mod is that Canadarm1 from? Also, how ya getting on with TNiC?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe Infernal Robotics Next\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"golkaidakhaana","CreatedById":206662,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T13:24:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223483421\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541669092\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192333\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Eaten by Black Hole\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Eaten by Black Hole said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe Infernal Robotics Next\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheesecake answered my question in the post above.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T13:43:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223481085\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541330814\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheesecake\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/4/2018 at 6:26 AM, Cheesecake said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- KU Band Antenna added\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill that work in 1.3.1?\u00A0 I loaded that mod and although the part is there in the files, it\u0027s decidedly unloaded in-game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T17:48:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223483490\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541684619\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill that work in 1.3.1?\u00A0 I loaded that mod and although the part is there in the files, it\u0027s decidedly unloaded in-game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will work in all KSP-Versions. I used it in 1.3.x, 1.4.x and 1.5.x.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T19:44:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHrm.\u00A0 I must not have the right files then. =(\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n**Edit:\u003Cbr\u003E\nNope, I have the right files, it\u0027s simply not loading.\u00A0 Have no idea why.\u00A0 It doesn\u0027t appear in the Communications section of the parts list.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-08T20:18:28Z\u0022 title=\u002211/08/2018 08:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by slaintemaith\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T20:33:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223483624\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541706281\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n44 minutes ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHrm.\u00A0 I must not have the right files then. =(\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n**Edit:\u003Cbr\u003E\nNope, I have the right files, it\u0027s simply not loading.\u00A0 Have no idea why.\u00A0 It doesn\u0027t appear in the Communications section of the parts list.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFolder is: GameData\\MrMeeb\\SPT\\Parts\\Utility\\KUBand\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInside are 4 files:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKUBand.cfg\u003Cbr\u003E\nKUband.mu\u003Cbr\u003E\nKUBand_Diffuse.dds\u003Cbr\u003E\nThumbs.db\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn 1.5.x I delete all other folders in GameData\\MrMeeb because the parts are included in Cormorant now. I left only the KUBand-Antenna. And it is loading\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-08T20:47:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\u00A0 I figured it out.\u00A0 It was:\u003Cbr\u003E\n1) My fault.\u003Cbr\u003E\n2) Stupid.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks for your help, though.\u00A0 =)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nDid you know that you shouldn\u0027t change the dir tree when you add part mods?\u003Cbr\u003E\nOr if you do, you need to reflect that in the part.cfg?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYeah.\u003Cbr\u003E\nDerp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-08T20:48:41Z\u0022 title=\u002211/08/2018 08:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 8, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by slaintemaith\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wrench Head","CreatedById":175503,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-10T18:33:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there any 1.5.1 carft files or even a drawing of how to build out these parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-10T19:25:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223484855\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541874831\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175503\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wrench Head\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, Wrench Head said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there any 1.5.1 carft files or even a drawing of how to build out these parts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can find the Craftfiles in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E. They works in 1.5.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wrench Head","CreatedById":175503,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-10T19:31:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks @Chesseccake\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote when using the\u00A0CA - Mk3 Orbiter Flight Testing craft file, I removed the cargo and lost fuel connection. Had to add line from main tank to Shuttle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-10T23:20:47Z\u0022 title=\u002211/10/2018 11:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 10, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Wrench Head\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T01:11:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso make sure you double-check all your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E and control surface configurations.\u00A0 I\u0027m 99% sure that the body flap is \u0022off\u0022 by default, as is nose-pitch \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E, and there\u0027s something wonky with the AFT \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E as well.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn addition: I put a control pod in the aft and angle it at the same as the OMS engines.\u00A0 I\u0027ll then use an action group to activate the OMS engines, gimbals, and change control to the aft pod.\u00A0 This tends to even out orbital maneuvers.\u00A0 You can also add reaction wheels to the back and front if you wish.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI also seem to recall something wonky with the landing gear in the downloaded .craft.\u003Cbr\u003E\nFact is I\u0027ve gotten used to rebuilding the CA shuttle from the component parts with nothing but real shuttle images.\u00A0 (Useful for getting the placement and dihedral of the wings and placement of the landing gear)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll in all, it\u0027s a GREAT shuttle.\u00A0 Made better with the Ultimate Shuttle IVA (if you\u0027re using 1.4.x \u002B) or Kermantech\u0027s IVA if you\u0027re at 1.3.x.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T10:04:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485032\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541898667\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn addition: I put a control pod in the aft and angle it at the same as the OMS engines.\u00A0 I\u0027ll then use an action group to activate the OMS engines, gimbals, and change control to the aft pod.\u00A0 This tends to even out orbital maneuvers.\u00A0 You can also add reaction wheels to the back and front if you wish.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy? The OMS are perfectly aligned for this Shuttle so that it fly straight.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223484879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541878319\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175503\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wrench Head\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Wrench Head said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks @Chesseccake\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote when using the\u00A0CA - Mk3 Orbiter Flight Testing craft file, I removed the cargo and lost fuel connection. Had to add line from main tank to Shuttle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats why the crossfeed is off by default. Activate it in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E and you don\u0060t need a fuelline.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wuwuk","CreatedById":138928,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T12:54:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy \u0022Shuttle Lifting Body\u0022 does not want to be installed through the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003Eckan\u003C/abbr\u003E?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy KSP version 1.5.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-11T12:57:33Z\u0022 title=\u002211/11/2018 12:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Wuwuk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xD-FireStriker","CreatedById":137214,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T12:55:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485269\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541940849\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138928\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wuwuk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Wuwuk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy \u0022Shuttle Lifting Body\u0022 does not want to be installed through the skan?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy KSP version 1.5.1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dont this this mod is on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T13:46:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485212\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541930647\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheesecake\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Cheesecake said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy? The OMS are perfectly aligned for this Shuttle so that it fly straight.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn real life, that is absolutely true.\u00A0 In KSP, they really aren\u0027t.\u00A0 At least not as far as MechJeb\u00A0 or sane control is concerned.\u00A0 With the angled pod, a d/v change will keep your nose pointed mostly in the same spot as you finish your maneuver.\u00A0 Without it, you wind up \u0027chasing the needle.\u0027\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried it with and without a rear,\u00A0angled pod, and I assure you \u0027with\u0027 is better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-11T14:36:38Z\u0022 title=\u002211/11/2018 02:36  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by slaintemaith\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T15:35:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485289\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541943972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn real life, that is absolutely true.\u00A0 In KSP, they really aren\u0027t.\u00A0 At least not as far as MechJeb\u00A0 or sane control is concerned.\u00A0 With the angled pod, a d/v change will keep your nose pointed mostly in the same spot as you finish your maneuver.\u00A0 Without it, you wind up \u0027chasing the needle.\u0027\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried it with and without a rear,\u00A0angled pod, and I assure you \u0027with\u0027 is better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0060s not true. I have made hundreds of flights (last one is 10 minuts ago) in KSP with Cormorant-Shuttles and other Shuttles (with and without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E). And I didn\u0060t need some extra control pods or something. If the thrust of the OMS is correctly aligned to the center of mass it works 100% without other control pods or something.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also used the craft-files of cormorant. And I didn\u0060t need any controlpods or extra reaction wheels too.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo I think you do anything wrong with your shuttles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T15:42:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd you tweak your OMS before each flight to account for the differing center of mass due to payload?\u003Cbr\u003E\nI don\u0027t.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love to see some in-game footage to demonstrate how stable your shuttle maneuvers are.\u00A0 Maybe I\u0027m missing something.\u00A0 It\u0027s happened before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-11T15:48:47Z\u0022 title=\u002211/11/2018 03:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by slaintemaith\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T16:53:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541950920\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd you tweak your OMS before each flight to account for the differing center of mass due to payload?\u003Cbr\u003E\nI don\u0027t.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love to see some in-game footage to demonstrate how stable your shuttle maneuvers are.\u00A0 Maybe I\u0027m missing something.\u00A0 It\u0027s happened before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I tweaked nothing. With cormorant I attached the OMS one time normally to the OMS-Pods and saved this craftfile. That\u0060s it. The OMS must not 100% perfect. That\u0060s not possible with various payload. But with the buils-in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E of the Cockpit and, in extreme Situation, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E it will be fly perfect and stable. This works also with the originally craftfiles of CA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut a little question: which OMS do you use? the angled or the straight ones? I use the angled like the original SpaceShuttle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T17:02:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is as good a demonstration as I can give...(And I apologize for the sound not being in sync.\u00A0 I have no idea what\u0027s up with that)\u003Cbr\u003E\nWithout: (and this is the orignial .craft file)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/nk-WxTpynB0?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/xSydjhJr8DU?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-11T17:09:04Z\u0022 title=\u002211/11/2018 05:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by slaintemaith\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrBackjack","CreatedById":3449,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-11T19:49:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485032\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541898667\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition: I put a control pod in the aft and angle it at the same as the OMS engines.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s such a good Idea. A little annoying having to constantly pitch in circles when a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E maneuver gets to sub 1 m/s. And having the thrust vector\u00A0aligned with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E means it\u0027s not aligned with the nose vector, the vector \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E actually uses for pointing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T02:53:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541955180\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022138400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cheesecake\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Cheesecake said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, I tweaked nothing. \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love to know how you managed this, because I sure cannot as the above videos prove.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"harits","CreatedById":191726,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T03:27:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis mod haven\u0027t shuttle/buran gear?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\ni like reusable spacecraft in career mode\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cheesecake","CreatedById":138400,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T08:25:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223485639\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119951\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221541991202\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002214568\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022slaintemaith\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, slaintemaith said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love to know how you managed this, because I sure cannot as the above videos prove.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake a Maneuvernode with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E and fly ist per hand. I know that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E had problems with angled engines in the past and don\u0060t know if they fixed it. But: it is no problem of any shuttle like cormorant or the old CSS-Shuttle/DECQs-Shuttle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"slaintemaith","CreatedById":14568,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-12T13:15:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh.\u00A0 Nope.\u00A0 I don\u0027t do orbital ops in KSP by hand if I can possibly avoid it.\u00A0 I barely like flying in the atmo manually the controls are so bloody awful.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnd \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E \u003Cem\u003Edoesn\u0027t \u003C/em\u003Ehave problems with angled engines: if you angle the control point to match it.\u003Cbr\u003E\n...which was sort of my entire point.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf I wanted to control the ship manually, I\u0027d not bother with it at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}